header.gameNote: USF INVITATIONAL AT SAN FRANCISCO CA

article.headline: New Mexico State 78, Chicago St 63
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Mike Mitchell scored 19 points and was one of five New Mexico State players in double figures as the Aggies beat Chicago State 78-63 Saturday night in the consolation game of the USF Invitational. New Mexico State (3-4) built a 15-point lead in the first half, saw it cut to four early in the second before reasserting themselves in the final stretch. Chicago State (1-5) was led by reserve forward Kourtney Calvin, who scored 21 points and grabbed 12 rebounds. Royce Parran, who had 35 in the Cougars' loss to Fullerton a night earlier, finished with 18. The Aggies used an 11-2 run midway in the first half to build their 15-point margin. Ted Knauber finished the spurt with a 3-point shot from deep in the corner that made the score 28-13. But the Cougars turned up the pressure with their defense and scored nine straight of their own, six from Calvin, to knock the New Mexico State lead back down to six at the half 41-35. Calvin opened the second half with a slam dunk that cut the margin to four, but that's as close as Chicago State would get. With New Mexico State up by five, Tyrone Nelson tipped in an Aggie miss, David Fisher put home a short jumper and Mitchell hit a layin to push the lead to double figures. It would grow to 17 at 68-51. Nelson added 14 for New Mexico State, Knauber had 11 and Kevin Ford and Shaun Davis had 10. Chicago State, which missed its first seven free throw attempts, finished 16-for-26 from the line.
